conserve /kənˈsɜːv/

(conserving,conserved,conserves) 

1. V-T If you conserve a supply of something, you use it carefully so that it lasts for a long time. 节省 

例： The factories have closed for the weekend to conserve energy. 这些工厂在那个周末关了厂以节省能源。 

2. V-T To conserve something means to protect it from harm, loss, or change. 保护 

例： ...a big increase in U.S. aid to help developing countries conserve their forests. …美国对帮助发展中国家保护森林的援助的大幅增加。

